===Noun===
{{en-noun|xyla}}
# {{lb|en|historical}} A [[unit]] of [[length]] in [[Ancient Greece]].
#* '''2020''', Roger S. Bagnall, ‎Alexander Jones, ''Mathematics, Metrology, and Model Contracts'' (page 81)
#*: The '''xylon''', in which naubia are measured. The royal ('''xylon''') 9 comprises 3 cubits, 18 palms, 72 fingers; 10 the private ('''xylon''') comprises 2&frac23; cubits, 16 palms, 64 fingers, so that the surveyor's schoinion comprises 32 royal '''xyla''', and 36 private ('''xyla''').
